Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.07,0:01:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,An odd man approached me while\NI was resting in the bamboo forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.58,0:01:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, are you a traveler?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.50,0:01:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.75,0:01:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You must be leaving the mountain then.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.96,0:01:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I'm headed west.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.01,0:01:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That's great.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.18,0:02:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you mind if I walk with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.76,0:02:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you lost?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.60,0:02:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I just can't get out of the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.94,0:02:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You must have a really bad sense of direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.36,0:02:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been troubling me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.40,0:02:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been three years since anyone came by.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.15,0:02:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Three years?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.86,0:02:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I know it's weird, but I haven't been\Nable to leave here the whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.58,0:02:35.59,ep-title-bg,,0,0,0,,{\fad(2000,0)\p1\blur1}m 0 0 l 950 0 950 100 0 100
Dialogue: 1,0:02:29.58,0:02:35.59,ep-title,,0,0,0,,{\fad(2100,0)\be1}Inside the Cage
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.17,0:02:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm from the village at the base of the mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.64,0:02:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you're a local then.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.81,0:02:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not like you can't see the sun.\NI don't see how you could get lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.73,0:02:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't understand either.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.23,0:02:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, this is a huge forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.67,0:03:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Shit. We're back here again.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.21,0:03:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What the hell's happening? My compass isn't broken.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.47,0:03:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We were headed west at first.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.18,0:03:27.93,Default,,0,0,0,,But we gradually wandered off track...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.43,0:03:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and ended up doing a full lap.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.44,0:03:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly. You can't go where you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.86,0:03:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What the hell?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.65,0:03:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You must've been caught too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.24,0:03:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You wanna live here with us for now?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.29,0:03:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,No way, damn it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.04,0:03:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,There's others here, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.75,0:03:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, there was a family that was living here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.97,0:04:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Kisuke.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.30,0:04:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The mother's not alive anymore,\Nbut her daughter is my wife now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.64,0:04:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We've known each other since we\Nwere little. I guess it's not all bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.23,0:04:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.52,0:04:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,He's a traveler. We were just chatting.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.27,0:04:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,She's my wife, Setsu.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.44,0:04:26.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry to make you put up with this, Ginko-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.49,0:04:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to go home now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.87,0:04:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You wanna rest with us?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.04,0:04:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I'm going to see if I can figure something out.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.46,0:04:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.79,0:04:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then, take care.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.59,0:04:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}"Take care"?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.84,0:04:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Rather odd.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.06,0:04:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I made it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.86,0:05:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That sucked.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.16,0:05:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Need something?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.24,0:05:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you came out of the forest, did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.91,0:05:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.95,0:05:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you see a man inside?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.08,0:05:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, is he being teased or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.13,0:05:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.84,0:05:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,He's been possessed by a monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.97,0:05:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You're lucky you're safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.06,0:05:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,A monster?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.02,0:05:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Stop that!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.14,0:05:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a white bamboo tree growing...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.06,0:05:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You're ruining the village's reputation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.24,0:05:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Ginko-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.99,0:05:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You couldn't get out?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.83,0:05:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I just came back because I wanted to see something.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.92,0:06:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard in the village there's\Na white bamboo tree here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.67,0:06:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm a bit curious about you and your wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.88,0:06:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you intend to do when you see it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.72,0:06:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,If it happens to be in my area of expertise,\NI'd want to hear more about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.31,0:06:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a really rare phenomenon.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.19,0:06:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I might even be able to find a way to get you out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.53,0:06:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Unless you don't want me to\Nbarge in; then I'll do it alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.20,0:06:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,This way.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.92,0:06:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,There's four more aside from this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.47,0:06:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's a "Magaridake".
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.81,0:07:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,First, can you tell me everything that happened here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.86,0:07:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a story that the kids in\Nmy village were raised with.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.95,0:07:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,A young couple lived in the bamboo forest here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.37,0:07:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,They've been trying for years to have children,\Nand the husband often left home.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.17,0:07:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The wife was a strange woman\Nwho would talk to the plants.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.59,0:07:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,At night she would wander through the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.13,0:07:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Then there was a time when she said she was pregnant.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.64,0:07:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Suspicious, her husband followed her.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.56,0:07:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.19,0:07:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,He found her vacantly clinging\Nonto a white bamboo tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.32,0:07:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,He ran away frightened, but he was berated\Nby the villagers, and returned home.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.37,0:08:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,There he found his wife embracing a bamboo\Nsprout as if it were her baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.17,0:08:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,She gave birth to a bamboo sprout?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.21,0:08:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what he said, apparently.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.63,0:08:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,She wasn't just trying to irritate her husband?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.93,0:08:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,He ran from the village in the end, so we thought so too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.35,0:08:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,In reality, when we saw the "bamboo child",\Nshe just looked like any other girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.44,0:08:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That was Setsu.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.90,0:08:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Her mother was gone by then,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.95,0:08:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,so me, my sister and my friends often\Nplayed here to keep her company.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.12,0:08:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We did think Setsu was unusual, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.71,0:08:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,She'd only drink water, and she'd never leave the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.21,0:08:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But we all liked her.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.38,0:08:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,At some point, we were trapped in the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.97,0:09:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We wandered around, and eventually,\None by one, the others disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.94,0:09:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,All of a sudden, I was alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.86,0:09:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone came looking for me the day after,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.28,0:09:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,but they just couldn't leave when I was with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.41,0:09:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You knew I was going to get trapped, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.21,0:09:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry. I was curious if outsiders might get trapped too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.71,0:09:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I lived at Setsu's place ever since.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.47,0:09:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I had no relatives other than my sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.18,0:09:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The villagers all helped us out with food and such.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.31,0:09:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,My sister and I were pretty much raised by the villagers.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.06,0:09:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We were all like family. It was a nice village.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.65,0:09:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But the longer we lived like that,\Nthe less people came to visit.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.53,0:10:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Kisuke, are you lonely?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.21,0:10:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.67,0:10:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.42,0:10:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,In time, Setsu became pregnant.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.92,0:10:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.52,0:10:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That's when I first realized...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.77,0:10:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,what Setsu really was.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.99,0:10:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The midwife ran back to the village,\Nand no one's come here since.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.83,0:10:45.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I know it's hard to believe.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.16,0:10:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.87,0:10:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So what's this "Magaridake" you speak of?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.09,0:10:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Contrary to its name, it's not a plant.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.76,0:11:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,A bamboo forest shares a single root.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.01,0:11:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,All together they make up a whole.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.47,0:11:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Or, you can say they're different members of the same family.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.44,0:11:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Magaridake are "Mushi" that infect the roots\Nand play on as members of the family.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.11,0:11:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,They consume nutrients from the root,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.90,0:11:21.95,Default,,0,0,0,,but they also return chemicals that\Ncause the bamboo to grow.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.45,0:11:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,They expand the forest and create new stocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.79,0:11:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Your wife is half Mushi, half human.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.29,0:11:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We Mushi-shi call such a person an "Oniko".
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.92,0:11:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,They are rare "hybrids".
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.42,0:11:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's bothering you, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.05,0:11:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.84,0:11:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I've already seen our daughter be born.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.26,0:11:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter what her mother was, Setsu is herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.39,0:11:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The villagers don't seem to think so, but I\Nthink they'd understand if they met her.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.90,0:12:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,We might be able to live in the village, the three of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.20,0:12:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's why you're trying to get out of the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.53,0:12:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.16,0:12:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, I'm worried about my sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.08,0:12:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,She might be having a hard time because of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.67,0:12:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got an idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.81,0:12:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Connecting all the points where\Nwe change direction unwillingly,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.07,0:12:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}it forms a near-perfect circle.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.82,0:12:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You can't go where you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.50,0:12:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The center of the circle is that tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.63,0:13:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that your "Water of life"?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.10,0:13:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.31,0:13:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Could I have some?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.44,0:13:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, my mother told me\Nnot to share it with anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.78,0:13:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Not even with Kisuke?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.41,0:13:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I did give it to him once.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.83,0:13:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Back when we were children.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.58,0:13:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, does it bother you that the villagers hate you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.01,0:13:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It does.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.51,0:13:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm happy so long as I have\NKisuke and our daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.97,0:13:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I sympathize with Kisuke because he can't get out.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.68,0:13:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm glad for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.65,0:14:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Forgive me for doing this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.21,0:14:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew it, I can't get out.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.63,0:14:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.60,0:14:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The leaves are gonna fall this year too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.90,0:14:50.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Your bamboo mommy's giving you leaf\Nmeals so that you can grow big.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.41,0:14:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Which one is Mommy?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.12,0:14:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Every one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.83,0:14:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone is raising their children.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.83,0:15:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Daddy remembers the village\Naround this time of the year.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.63,0:15:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It's open, and so bright.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.72,0:15:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a lively village.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.93,0:15:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish I could show it to you too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.29,0:15:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll be okay, won't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.75,0:15:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Kisuke will be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.42,0:15:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So you know what the cause is?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.51,0:15:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.64,0:15:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Mushi, unlike plants, have consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.26,0:16:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,They command the various parts of\Ntheir body to carry out their will.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.06,0:16:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The body for this Mushi is the whole\Nforest surrounding this one tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.44,0:16:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's this water that Setsu drinks\Nthat passes on the will.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.16,0:16:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Normal water doesn't respond to the tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.83,0:16:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Just holding this water makes you\Naffected by the Mushi's will.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.30,0:16:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, anyone who drinks the water,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.93,0:16:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and anyone near such a person are affected as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.39,0:16:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's hot today.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.52,0:16:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm getting thirsty.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.44,0:16:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'll give you a sip.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.23,0:16:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think Setsu would have known.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.90,0:16:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.36,0:16:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But then what should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.41,0:17:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We probably have to get the water out of your body,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.08,0:17:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,but honestly, I can't think of a way to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.75,0:17:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,There's one more way...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.50,0:17:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,But I wouldn't want to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.30,0:17:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no telling what kind of\Nadverse effect it might cause.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.30,0:17:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I... see.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.73,0:17:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.44,0:17:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I can finally give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.00,0:17:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.63,0:17:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,held Kisuke back for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.38,0:17:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.89,0:17:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.19,0:18:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.49,0:18:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You wouldn't be able to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.66,0:18:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You're its progeny.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.28,0:18:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You're part of its body.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.33,0:18:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like your arms and legs can't deny your mind's will.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.54,0:18:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Were you listening the whole time?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.00,0:18:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Kisuke... it's my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.88,0:18:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,But Kisuke wasn't misfortunate.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.64,0:18:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Kisuke brought me happiness despite what I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.68,0:18:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet I stole his village from him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.98,0:18:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,He even told me,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.73,0:18:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,"Whatever my mother is, I'm me."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.04,0:19:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.69,0:19:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Setsu!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.73,0:19:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Where'd she go?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.75,0:19:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the village!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.83,0:19:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, it's me, Kisuke!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.25,0:19:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I finally got out!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.96,0:19:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.47,0:20:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, how have you been?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.88,0:20:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that the kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.80,0:20:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.89,0:20:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Go back!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.97,0:20:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.31,0:20:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't bring that thing here!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.19,0:20:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a child too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.61,0:20:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't make my child miserable.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.24,0:20:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, where's Mommy?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.91,0:20:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.33,0:20:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go back.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.80,0:20:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,They lived happily for some time after.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.31,0:20:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But half a year later,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.48,0:20:57.15,Default,,0,0,0,,when I went to see the effect of having\Ncut down the mother stock...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.61,0:21:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Not a single Magaridake.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.03,0:21:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It's you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.21,0:21:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,All the white trees wilted away one after another.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.88,0:21:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,They lived on that water.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.63,0:21:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,They were in pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.51,0:21:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,By the time I buried them here,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.85,0:21:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,they crumbled like dead trees.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.48,0:21:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Setsu shouldn't have done it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.77,0:21:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It was Setsu's mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.49,0:21:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I made her do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.78,0:21:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I couldn't give up on the village.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.46,0:22:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's that time of the year again, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.80,0:22:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,A white tree. Since when?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.56,0:22:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Babies' voices.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.23,0:22:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's coming from their graves.
